# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) and set values for your environment.
# https://vite.dev/guide/env-and-mode.html
#
# QA checklist (register on server, CORS, 413): docs/testing-plan-dataset-upload.md

# Backend origin for API calls. Default when unset: `/api` (Vite dev server proxies to :8000).
# For a remote API, set the full origin and add it to PYPEDEID_CORS_ORIGINS on the API.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000

# Sent as `X-API-Key` on every request when the API enforces keys.
# For **inference** (POST /process/*, review flows): use an **inference**-scoped key.
# For **Register on server** (POST /datasets/upload, line_format=production_v1): you need
# **api_key_scope=admin** — set an **admin** key here, or use open API in local dev.
# GET /health returns api_key_scope (admin | inference | null) for the key sent; the UI uses it to enable/disable Register.
# Large JSONL: raise PYPEDEID_MAX_BODY_BYTES on the API or uploads return 413.
# VITE_API_KEY=
